item.title: TES KONTEN
item.description: When I began working on the computer full time earlier this year, I was still using the GUIs of my computer and had little intuition for how to organize my work in a coding Environment. Now I use exclusively the command line to navigate my MacBook Pro; collaborate and track my work using Github; and I write most assignments, and now blog posts in markdown. The largest behavioral change for me was working primarily in text editors, Github, and the command line.
